    <tr>
      <th>2</th>
      <td>erasureCodingDelay</td>
      <td>Integer</td>
      <td>Specifies the erasure coding delay for the erasure coding topology as a number of\ndays. Valid values are integers in the range zero through 3,650. The default is zero.</td>
      <td>This property is optional on a PUT request.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>3</th>
      <td>fullCopy</td>
      <td>Boolean</td>
      <td>Specifies whether the erasure coding topology uses full-copy distribution or chunk\ndistribution. Valid values are:\ntrue\nThe erasure coding topology uses full-copy distribution.\nfalse\nThe erasure coding topology uses chunk distribution.\nThe default is false.</td>
      <td>This property is optional on a PUT request.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>4</th>
      <td>hcpSystems</td>
      <td>List</td>
      <td>Lists the HCP systems that are included in the erasure coding topology. Each system\nis identified by the fully qualified name of the domain associated with the\n[[hcp_system]] network on that system.</td>
      <td>This property is not valid on a PUT or POST request.\nIn XML, the element that identifies each system is\nname. In JSON, the name in the name/value pair that\nlists the systems is name.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>5</th>
      <td>id</td>
      <td>String</td>
      <td>Specifies the ID for the erasure coding topology.</td>
      <td>This property is not valid on a PUT or POST request.\nIt is returned only by a verbose GET request.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>6</th>
      <td>minimumObjectSize</td>
      <td>Long</td>
      <td>Specifies the minimum size for objects to be erasure coded. Valid values are:\n4096\n16384\n32768\n65536\n131072\n262144\n524288\n1048576\nThe default is 4096.</td>
      <td>This property is optional on a PUT request.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>7</th>
      <td>name</td>
      <td>String</td>
      <td>Specifies the name of the erasure coding topology. The name must be from one\nthrough 64 characters long and can contain any valid UTF-8 characters, including\nwhite space. Erasure coding topology names are not case sensitive.</td>
      <td>This property is required on a PUT request.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>8</th>
      <td>protectionStatus</td>
      <td>String</td>
      <td>Specifies the current status of the erasure coding topology with respect to how well-\nprotected erasure-coded objects are. Possible values are:\nBROKEN\nTwo or more systems in the topology are unavailable. Objects erasure coded\naccording to the topology are inaccessible and are not protected.\nHEALTHY\nAll systems in the topology are available. Objects erasure coded according to\nthe topology can be read and are fully protected.\nRETIRED\nThe topology has finished retiring.\nRETIRING\nThe topology is in the process of retiring.\nUNKNOWN\nHCP cannot determine the protection status.\nVULNERABLE\nOne system in the topology is unavailable, and the loss of a link or\nsuspension of activity on a link would prevent an additional system from\nreceiving data or chunks for newly ingested objects. Objects erasure coded\naccording to the topology can be read but are not fully protected.</td>
      <td>This property is not valid on a PUT or POST request.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>9</th>
      <td>readStatus</td>
      <td>String</td>
      <td>Specifies the current status of the erasure coding topology with respect to the ability\nto read erasure-coded objects. Possible values are:\nBROKEN\nTwo or more systems in the topology are unavailable. Objects erasure coded\naccording to the topology are inaccessible.\nHEALTHY\nAll systems in the topology are available. Objects erasure coded according to\nthe topology can be read.\nRETIRED\nThe topology has finished retiring.\nUNKNOWN\nHCP cannot determine the read status.\nVULNERABLE</td>
      <td>This property is not valid on a PUT or POST request.</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
